The most important traits for a modern professional laptop are power and portability, and the ASUS ExpertBook B9 delivers both of these without compromise. Combining powerful hardware with an impressive, lightweight frame, the ExpertBook B9 is built to be used in any environment, whether you are on the move or at the office. The ASUS ExpertBook B9 won the Red Dot award for 2020 for its cutting-edge design, which is ultra-thin and weighs less than 1kg. It also sports a touchpad that doubles as a touch-screen number pad for added productivity when connected to peripherals. This innovative design, paired with all-day battery life and cutting-edge connectivity options, makes the ASUS ExpertBook B9 an attractive choice for high-end professionals. The ASUS ExpertBook B9 is not only a small and light professional laptop, it also has some serious power under the hood. The model shown here is equipped with an Intel Core i7-10510U processor, 16GB of RAM, and a 1TB PCIe SSD for high-speed data storage. These specifications mean the device is capable of handling all the standard workloads thrown at it without breaking a sweat. It’s connectivity suite and impressive battery life make it suitable for any working environment, too, from working remotely in a coffee shop to a standard office environment. A range of physical ports then allow you to plug in external monitors and peripherals, and it includes an Ethernet port. The ASUS ExpertBook B9 also offers Wi-Fi 6 connectivity, allowing you to take advantage of high-speed Internet without being tethered to a wired connection. Unlike many other lightweight laptops, the ASUS ExpertBook B9 delivers truly impressive battery life. The notebook’s 66Wh battery provides up to 24 hours of battery life on a single charge and supports fast-charge technology. This allows you to recharge the device up to 60% capacity in as little as 39 minutes. The power efficiency of the laptop complements the long-life battery and makes no compromise in terms of performance within professional tasks. The greatest feature of the laptop, though, is its design – offering a rare combination of exceptional performance and battery life in an ultra-thin form factor, while retaining connectivity features and high-end functionality. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-426058" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-1.jpg" alt="ASUS ExpertBook B9 1" width="640" height="450" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-1.jpg 1280w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-1-300x211.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-1-1024x720.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-1-768x540.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-1-1200x844.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-426068" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-6.jpg" alt="ASUS ExpertBook B9 6" width="640" height="450" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-6.jpg 1280w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-6-300x211.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-6-1024x720.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-6-768x540.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-6-1200x844.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-426066" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/ASUS-ExpertBook-B9-5.jpg" alt="A